00:56:35.410 --> 00:56:36.340
Well, yeah.

00:56:36.340 --> 00:56:39.554
Let's face it, to me, I like unsweet tea.

00:56:51.908 --> 00:56:52.205
I can drink it like water.

00:56:55.800 --> 00:56:55.980
She says it's just dyed water, Brandon.

00:56:56.160 --> 00:57:01.080
I can drink unsweet tea all day long, more than water.

00:57:11.210 --> 00:57:11.460
But there's water in it, so I consider it water.

00:57:11.460 --> 00:57:12.960
Be the best you.

00:57:12.960 --> 00:57:14.820
That's what I'm trying to say.

00:57:14.820 --> 00:57:15.719
Start this year.

00:57:15.719 --> 00:57:17.394
We've got four weeks left.

00:57:17.394 --> 00:57:20.879
Start out with your mindset changing—changing things of getting out of debt.

00:57:20.879 --> 00:57:27.040
Changing things of how do you get your marriage better?

00:57:28.640 --> 00:57:37.326
And that's my main focus is always trying to make our marriage better and keep us going, and saying, "Listen, how do we?

00:57:53.804 --> 00:57:54.000
" And that's why we survived with a child with special needs.

00:58:07.787 --> 00:58:08.062
Like I said, 75% of all marriages quit in divorce, especially with a child with autism.

00:58:14.330 --> 00:58:14.520
And I told her, I said, "I refuse to be a statistic.

00:58:14.520 --> 00:58:18.457
" You know, how bad do you want change in your life?

00:58:19.131 --> 00:58:26.657
And that's why so many people said, "Brandon, how do you hear God?

00:58:26.657 --> 00:58:33.977
How do you have a relationship with the Father?

00:58:35.280 --> 00:58:37.040
" I don't look at it as a chore.

00:58:37.040 --> 00:58:38.617
I really enjoy praying.

00:58:57.176 --> 00:58:57.344
I really enjoy spending time with Him.

00:59:09.839 --> 00:59:16.489
And Diana and I always talk about—she goes, "Brandon, is that something that's always been inside of you?

00:59:16.489 --> 00:59:19.073
Have you always been that way?

00:59:30.400 --> 00:59:32.249
" I said, "No, I think it's like some people say: Brandon, when you eat greens, you start getting a habit of eating greens because it starts—I say it tastes like trash, but I want to eat it more.

00:59:32.249 --> 00:59:35.439
You start craving it.

00:59:39.090 --> 00:59:42.240
" And what you feed on the most, you crave.

00:59:42.240 --> 00:59:44.550
And I really believe it's the truth.

00:59:44.550 --> 00:59:52.213
The more I crave Him, the more I read books—these little books.

00:59:55.143 --> 00:59:57.400
We had somebody send us a bunch of them.

01:00:04.949 --> 01:00:12.048
The more I crave Him, the more I seek Him, the more I find Him.

01:00:12.640 --> 01:00:23.200
And I just encourage every single one of you in this little time I always spend with you talking to you a little bit to crave Him.

01:00:23.200 --> 01:00:24.340
Find Him this year.

01:00:24.340 --> 01:00:27.309
He said, "Those that seek Me will find Me.

01:00:27.309 --> 01:00:28.933
" That has a—it's showing pursuit.

01:00:28.933 --> 01:00:31.234
Those that seek Me will find Me.

01:00:41.509 --> 01:00:41.779
That means you're pursuing.

01:00:41.779 --> 01:00:45.440
You're in hot pursuit.

01:00:45.440 --> 01:00:48.960
How bad, how desperate do you want it?

01:00:53.440 --> 01:00:55.871
And to me, it's like these little things that He tells me to do because He wants me to live.

01:00:55.871 --> 01:01:00.456
He goes, "Brandon," and in my dreams He'll talk to me.

01:01:00.456 --> 01:01:04.746
"I'm trying to tell you this because I want you to stay alive.

01:01:08.008 --> 01:01:08.720
I have much for you to do.

01:01:08.720 --> 01:01:11.739
I'm not trying to be mean.

01:01:20.660 --> 01:01:21.000
I just want you to live long and finish strong.

01:01:28.622 --> 01:01:28.960
" And I say, "Okay.

01:01:34.231 --> 01:01:35.164
" I gave you a little girl that loves to cook.

01:01:35.164 --> 01:01:47.486
Buy salmon and some greens and have her do it and get practice and tell her to watch YouTube videos on how to cook it.

01:01:47.486 --> 01:01:53.920
And Paisley would go in there because Diana's slamming busy.

01:01:54.760 --> 01:01:55.880
I mean, all the time.

01:02:00.506 --> 01:02:00.888
I told her, I said, "Are you okay to talk?

01:02:16.439 --> 01:02:16.799
Because I know you all keep her spinning.

01:02:16.799 --> 01:02:18.383
" I go, "Good Lord, these people.

01:02:18.383 --> 01:02:24.640
" But I'm thankful for it and I'm not complaining.

01:02:24.640 --> 01:02:38.179
But I'm so thankful because even whenever it's like cooking and Paisley learning how to make breads and things like that, she is gifted at it.

01:02:38.179 --> 01:02:42.799
She is really gifted at it.

01:02:42.799 --> 01:02:47.405
And she goes, "Daddy, look what I made you today.

01:02:47.405 --> 01:02:51.616
" It was sitting in there and I said, "What did you make me?

01:02:51.616 --> 01:03:01.457
" She said, "I got that salmon in there and she cooked it all up and she had it—I watched how to make it to perfection.

01:03:01.457 --> 01:03:07.324
" She went in there, she goes, "Did I put too much salt?

01:03:07.475 --> 01:03:10.480
" I said, "Oh, it was a little bit that time.

01:03:18.347 --> 01:03:18.569
" But that was okay.

01:03:22.736 --> 01:03:23.248
It was good.

01:03:26.319 --> 01:03:26.586
But she's practicing.

01:03:29.680 --> 01:03:39.200
And last night after I got finished, I was hungry and that salmon was waiting and she had that little meat there and the little stuff and it was perfect.

01:03:49.288 --> 01:03:49.616
And I went, "Wow, good job.

01:03:49.616 --> 01:03:54.480
" She's one of those chefs that doesn't have to measure.

01:03:54.480 --> 01:04:00.479
She just eyeballs it and she knows.

01:04:00.479 --> 01:04:02.639
She's good at it.

01:04:03.839 --> 01:04:08.240
Yeah, she's very good at 10 years old.

01:04:08.240 --> 01:04:11.000
She is a cooking machine, man.

01:04:17.727 --> 01:04:17.959
I was like, "Wow, look at you.

01:04:17.959 --> 01:04:22.160
" She goes, "I made the dessert.

01:04:33.333 --> 01:04:33.689
I'm not eating it.

01:04:33.689 --> 01:04:36.799
Don't make me desserts no more.

01:04:36.799 --> 01:04:41.369
" Because she can make cake like—oh my goodness, I taught her homemade cakes.

01:04:44.799 --> 01:04:45.976
I taught her how to mill the flour and she mills flour and she can make...

01:04:46.836 --> 01:04:50.879
and I didn't realize how many different kinds of wheats there were.

01:04:50.879 --> 01:04:54.400
"What's my favorite wheat?

01:05:16.978 --> 01:05:17.280
The berry.

01:05:17.280 --> 01:05:22.103
The mill.

01:05:22.103 --> 01:05:24.520
It's not the millet.

01:05:27.647 --> 01:05:28.255
" "I think you like the hard white, right?

01:05:32.400 --> 01:05:34.640
" Yeah.

01:05:34.640 --> 01:05:47.209
But there's all kinds of different kinds of wheats that Paisley mills the flour and does all things.

01:05:47.209 --> 01:06:05.056
She's been doing it for a while now, well over a year, but just listening and following things and listening to people.

01:06:05.056 --> 01:06:09.160
So, that's what I had for y'all.

01:06:13.351 --> 01:06:16.148
I know it's probably boring, but I'm trying to help inspire you to come up higher in 2026.

01:06:16.148 --> 01:06:19.120
Don't live another day like you did in 2025.

01:06:19.120 --> 01:06:20.879
Kamut, that's what you like.

01:06:20.879 --> 01:06:21.439
Kamut.

01:06:21.439 --> 01:06:23.199
Yeah, Kamut is the bomb.

01:06:23.199 --> 01:06:24.267
Think about it.

01:06:24.267 --> 01:06:26.133
So, all right.

01:06:26.133 --> 01:06:30.080
Well, you want to pray?

01:06:30.080 --> 01:06:31.623
Who wants to go?

01:06:31.623 --> 01:06:31.966
Ben?

01:06:50.583 --> 01:06:50.880
And I know I'm probably like, "Shut up, Brandon.

01:06:50.880 --> 01:06:56.400
" But hey, somebody might get blessed off of it.

01:06:56.400 --> 01:07:09.339
You know, you aren't hearing a lot of this stuff in church—people just being real with you, living this faith walk and living Christianity and doing it and being successful at it.

01:07:09.339 --> 01:07:12.107
Most of the leaders are not touchable.

01:07:12.551 --> 01:07:22.799
You go to a mega church and they're off the platform in five seconds and you don't even get to hear what they're saying.

01:07:22.799 --> 01:07:39.177
They'll tell you a little bit of a sermon for 30 minutes, but it's usually just to motivate you in your little way.

01:07:39.177 --> 01:07:43.566
You've got to keep your flame fanned.

01:07:49.920 --> 01:07:51.883
I want us to be successful and be champions like we're always taught at church.

01:07:57.039 --> 01:07:59.440
And He even said, Brandon, you do this for a year.

01:07:59.440 --> 01:08:04.519
She says it's just dyed water, Brandon.

01:08:12.559 --> 01:08:12.789
And that's why so many people said, Brandon, how do you hear God?

01:08:24.799 --> 01:08:28.427
But I'm so thankful because even whenever it's like cooking and Paisley learning how to make breads and things like that, she is gifted at it.

01:08:28.427 --> 01:08:32.480
She goes, Dad, I made the dessert.

01:08:33.520 --> 01:08:49.080
I taught her how to mill the flour and she mills flour and she can make, you know, and I didn't realize how many different kinds of wheats there was.

01:08:49.080 --> 01:08:56.959
But there's all kinds of wheats that Paisley mills the flour and does all things.

01:08:56.959 --> 01:08:58.640
Kamut, that's what you like.

01:08:58.640 --> 01:09:06.400
Of course !

01:09:06.400 --> 01:09:18.239
But is it really there to make you strong?

01:09:18.239 --> 01:09:28.159
I feel like there's a lot of anemic people.

01:09:28.159 --> 01:09:35.759
Diana and I have walked through the fire, and—I'm going to use the word—it sucks.

01:09:35.759 --> 01:09:53.040
There have been some very hard times, especially raising a child with special needs and going through things and thinking, "How are we going to make it?

01:09:53.040 --> 01:10:09.236
" Living on food stamps like we did for years, being a janitor, and her going through college and doing all the things that we've done, but we've made it work.

01:10:11.164 --> 01:10:17.840
And we always keep the main thing the main thing: keeping him first.

01:10:33.303 --> 01:10:33.611
And that's what I've tried to be—always that anchor in my house—to say, "Listen, we're going to serve God.

01:10:33.611 --> 01:10:36.540
We're going to pray as a family.

01:10:36.540 --> 01:10:40.377
We're going to take communion.

01:10:40.377 --> 01:10:45.632
We're going to seek him on Sundays.

01:10:45.632 --> 01:10:47.560
We're going to seek him on Mondays.

01:10:47.560 --> 01:10:49.028
We're going to seek him.

01:10:49.028 --> 01:10:56.237
And we're not just going to have a 30-minute sermon and out.

01:10:56.237 --> 01:11:03.520
We're going to make this real to us.

01:11:03.520 --> 01:11:29.931
" And the only way this is going to happen is if we go to a foundation, if we make this our spiritual gym that we do every single day.

01:11:29.931 --> 01:11:34.950
And we don't seek God like everybody else.

01:11:51.840 --> 01:11:52.080
We seek him.

01:11:52.080 --> 01:11:55.336
That's why I have visitations from him.

01:11:55.336 --> 01:12:08.176
And if there is anybody I would try to listen to, I try to listen to myself.

01:12:08.176 --> 01:12:13.680
And I don't mean that in an arrogant sense.

01:12:13.680 --> 01:12:18.183
But what we have is real and it's authentic.

01:12:18.183 --> 01:12:25.538
Even when people come over to work on the house, they go, "We feel the presence of God in here.

01:12:25.840 --> 01:12:27.475
" I say, "What do you feel?

01:12:27.475 --> 01:12:27.919
" "Peace.

01:12:27.919 --> 01:12:36.747
" And they start passing out on the couch if they sit down because they're looking for something.

01:12:36.747 --> 01:12:38.680
They find peace.

01:12:38.680 --> 01:12:42.160
And they'll lay down and they're out.

01:12:57.835 --> 01:13:02.953
I say, "Isn't that funny?

01:13:02.953 --> 01:13:12.206
They're finding their rest.

01:13:12.206 --> 01:13:41.910
" I want a place that Jesus can visit and where he feels comfortable with worship going on in the house.

01:13:41.920 --> 01:13:42.660
Praise.

01:14:08.897 --> 01:14:09.226
I say this house is a house of prayer.

01:14:43.679 --> 01:14:43.979
And I don't just let everybody come over.

01:15:10.272 --> 01:15:11.104
You know, you set your boundaries.

01:15:11.104 --> 01:15:18.880
That's what I'm trying to tell y'all.

01:15:18.880 --> 01:15:23.520
This is a house.

01:15:30.800 --> 01:15:31.507
I don't want your drama.

01:15:31.507 --> 01:15:40.320
So, I limit drama and how much I have in my life.

01:15:51.120 --> 01:15:51.387
It's too expensive for me.

01:15:51.387 --> 01:16:11.440
I've got to stay on that—I want to go vertical so that I hear him so well.

01:16:22.338 --> 01:16:22.676
I can't afford in the natural not to hear him.

01:17:03.663 --> 01:17:04.040
I need him.

01:17:34.800 --> 01:17:35.280
And drama causes distraction.

01:17:39.600 --> 01:17:40.080
I don't want drama.

01:17:40.080 --> 01:17:59.960
But I refuse, because I told her, "I don't make any decision—physically, financially, whatever—without having prayed about it first," even going around people.

01:18:37.720 --> 01:18:38.320
I listen, "Is that at peace with you?

01:18:44.488 --> 01:18:44.832
Is it okay?

01:18:44.832 --> 01:18:49.040
" And I question it all the time.

01:18:49.040 --> 01:18:51.619
I inquire of the Lord about everything.

01:19:38.420 --> 01:19:38.880
I do.

01:20:21.742 --> 01:20:22.106
And it's to the point where some people might think that's obnoxious.

01:20:22.106 --> 01:20:25.120
I inquire of the Lord.

01:20:25.120 --> 01:20:26.680
"What's today hold?

01:20:26.680 --> 01:20:28.717
What do you have?

01:20:28.717 --> 01:20:36.343
Where do you want us to go to church?

01:20:36.343 --> 01:20:39.960
Where do you want us to be?

01:20:50.032 --> 01:20:58.926
" I don't just go to church where I want to go to church; I go to church where he tells me to go.

01:21:20.360 --> 01:21:20.530
"I want you to go here.

01:21:50.320 --> 01:21:51.147
" "Well, I don't like going there.

01:22:00.194 --> 01:22:00.503
" "Well, that's where I want you to go.

01:22:00.503 --> 01:22:01.120
" Okay.

01:22:07.943 --> 01:22:39.096
Do you know how long I stayed at a church I could not stand until I found a church that I liked?

01:22:39.096 --> 01:23:03.703
Because he finally released me and then finally I was like, "Thank God, I like—you know, we can get something from here.

01:23:03.703 --> 01:23:21.700
" But we worked for a church that we didn't get anything out of for—was it 14 years?

01:23:29.600 --> 01:23:29.940
And it was rough.

01:23:29.940 --> 01:23:40.520
But he said, "Stay, pray, do what I've asked you to do.

01:23:40.520 --> 01:23:43.600
" And I inquired of him, "When, Lord?

01:23:43.600 --> 01:23:45.840
" and then he said, "Go here.

01:23:45.840 --> 01:23:49.303
" And I'm so thankful.

01:23:49.303 --> 01:23:59.554
And you go to the places and now you go, "Oh, this is refreshing.

01:23:59.554 --> 01:24:01.783
I'm so appreciative.

01:24:12.613 --> 01:24:19.440
" You appreciate the green pasture versus where you were, and you go, "Oh, Lord, you have—" you don't ever complain again.

01:24:27.490 --> 01:24:27.720
You go, "Oh, God.

01:24:27.720 --> 01:24:29.599
" Seriously, y'all, ain't that right?

01:24:30.559 --> 01:24:34.000
And you go, "Thank God for certain places now.

01:24:34.000 --> 01:24:34.827
" Right.

01:24:34.827 --> 01:24:35.653
Yeah.

01:24:35.653 --> 01:24:36.747
Thank God.

01:24:50.731 --> 01:24:51.086
And I try never to persuade you where you should go to church, ever.

01:24:51.086 --> 01:24:53.349
That's for the Holy Ghost to tell you.

01:24:53.349 --> 01:25:01.780
But some people, you tell me where you go to church and I go, "I would run as fast as I could.

01:25:01.780 --> 01:25:02.680
" Oh, no.

01:25:02.680 --> 01:25:06.000
But maybe the Lord's assigned you there.

01:25:06.000 --> 01:25:08.217
I just go, "Okay, we'll pray.

01:25:08.217 --> 01:25:09.382
Let's pray.

01:25:09.382 --> 01:25:10.159
Ready?

01:25:10.159 --> 01:25:11.531
" It's an hour.

01:25:11.531 --> 01:25:22.980
I'm just resting a little bit talking because when I pray the way I do and I'm seeing y'all, it's like putting 500 pounds on your back and running up a mountain.

01:25:28.440 --> 01:25:28.667
And when I get done, there's a lot of times I just crash.

01:25:34.069 --> 01:25:40.880
And I told Diana, "It's nice because Brandon likes to talk and just be friends with y'all.

01:25:40.880 --> 01:25:42.800
" It's just like—it's okay.

01:25:42.800 --> 01:25:47.130
I'm not delaying it; I'm just talking because I know it's coming.

01:25:47.130 --> 01:25:50.419
I know what he asked me to do.

01:25:50.419 --> 01:25:52.040
Hi, Diana.

01:25:52.040 --> 01:25:54.434
She's always quiet.

01:26:12.320 --> 01:26:12.667
"Well, I don't know, you put me on the spot.

01:26:12.667 --> 01:26:16.010
" Does anybody else here like unsweet iced tea?

01:26:16.010 --> 01:26:16.390
Yeah.

01:26:16.390 --> 01:26:30.639
Most said they like hot tea, which—I like iced tea, but they like hot tea.

01:26:30.639 --> 01:26:38.538
He likes hot tea, too.

01:27:07.680 --> 01:27:08.580
I'm not really a hot tea person; I'm an iced unsweet tea person.

01:27:08.580 --> 01:27:18.453
Some people say, "I like honey in it.

01:27:18.453 --> 01:27:23.040
" Ooh, honey sounds good.

01:27:23.040 --> 01:27:34.755
I like honey.

01:27:34.755 --> 01:27:46.548
Here we go.

01:27:46.548 --> 01:27:48.571
Hack two.

01:27:48.571 --> 01:28:01.048
Especially like Manuka honey.

01:28:01.048 --> 01:28:07.780
Talking about tea.

01:28:07.780 --> 01:28:31.999
I love honey.

01:28:34.400 --> 01:28:36.050
It's like a bear.

01:28:36.050 --> 01:28:38.800
I love honey.

01:28:38.800 --> 01:28:43.706
But not anymore.

01:28:44.688 --> 01:28:52.633
"You eat too much.

01:28:52.633 --> 01:29:33.073
" I said—Diana goes, "Do you realize how many calories you're eating in that honey?

01:29:33.073 --> 01:29:40.052
" I said, "Well, it's all natural.

01:29:40.052 --> 01:29:42.754
It's good.

01:29:59.280 --> 01:29:59.920
" And she said, "No, it's not.

01:29:59.920 --> 01:30:03.280
It's not good.

01:30:04.080 --> 01:30:10.651
You can't even do a couple.

01:30:10.651 --> 01:30:18.435
You can't do that.

01:30:52.507 --> 01:30:52.732
" I said, "But it's all good, organic.

01:31:01.989 --> 01:31:02.617
It's okay, baby.

01:31:06.720 --> 01:31:07.200
It's organic.

01:31:07.200 --> 01:31:11.520
" She said, "It's organic, is it?

01:31:11.520 --> 01:31:17.760
But look at the calorie count on a tablespoon.

01:31:17.760 --> 01:31:23.500
" I said, "Oh, but boy, honey's nice.

01:31:23.500 --> 01:31:30.153
" I got to make big changes.

01:31:30.153 --> 01:32:00.164
Father, I just thank you, Lord, for how good you've been to me.

01:32:00.164 --> 01:32:08.253
Just being real, Lord.

01:32:08.253 --> 01:32:41.110
People have so many issues and Father, you've delivered us from all of it.

01:33:47.760 --> 01:33:49.859
I know in my heart what you've said in your word and I do the best I can to follow it with all my heart.

01:33:49.859 --> 01:34:00.329
Father, we train up a child in the way they should go, and when they get older, they'll not depart from it.

01:34:00.329 --> 01:34:08.023
We pray, we seek you, we find—and you say we find you now.

01:34:08.023 --> 01:34:17.400
Father, I thank you that you become so real to the people on the other side of this camera.

01:34:17.400 --> 01:34:25.773
There's so many people that are just looking for a God they can talk to.

01:34:25.773 --> 01:34:41.801
They have their grandma's religion of the hermeneutics, theology, the Pharisee—you know, it's so bound.

01:35:00.844 --> 01:35:01.253
But God, you're not in that box; you're way out here.

01:35:22.560 --> 01:35:22.856
And you just want to be a friend.

01:35:22.856 --> 01:35:28.080
I just want a God I can talk to.

01:35:28.080 --> 01:35:38.229
I just want to be friends.

01:35:38.239 --> 01:35:43.440
And I want you to feel comfortable visiting me.

01:35:54.880 --> 01:35:55.160
That Father, that you become more real to me than the air that I breathe.

01:35:57.710 --> 01:36:03.600
You become more real to me than the food that I partake of every day.

01:36:18.400 --> 01:36:21.511
